Murray: Let’s resolve this looming crisis, and prevent a construction shutdown this summer for our economy, businesses, and families.
Murray: I am once again calling on Republicans to work with us in good faith to do the right thing and help us avoid a construction shutdown
Murray: We know bipartisan work is possible. We know the country is better when it happens, and it’s what the families we represent expect.
Murray: We should be able to agree on investing in and improving our transportation infrastructure—not letting it crumble.
Murray: Across the country, more than 1,000 construction projects could be at risk, according to @USDOT.
Murray: Instead of lurching to yet another crisis, and putting construction projects at risk—let’s work together and do the right thing.
Murray: If Congress fails to act, families, businesses, & states will see another shutdown, this time w/ highway projects around the country
Murray: The Highway Trust Fund needs more revenue to pay for critical projects in my home state & across the country.
Murray: #WA relies on the Highway Trust Fund to pay for construction projects to ease traffic, repair bridges, & make safety improvements.

Murray: If Congress passes this bill, working families next year could see a credit of $1600 for one child or $3200 for more than one child
Murray: The Helping Working Families Afford Child Care Act would boost the benefit working families can receive for #childcare costs.
Murray: This is a real problem for far too many hardworking parents—and it’s also a real problem for our economy.
Murray: For families below the poverty level…child care can, on average, swallow up a third of what parents are able to bring home.
Murray: We need to make sure our policies are updated to meet the needs of today’s working parents.
Murray: Legislation would give working parents the #FairShot they deserve.  #ChildCare

Join Sen. Murray, @RepRonKind @SSWorks @HRC *LIVE* at 3PM as they push for action on #SAMElove bill: http://www.murray.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/newsreleases?ID=f758a004-1930-45ad-95d8-6722be7efeba … #LGBT
Murray: This is an all-too-rare opportunity for all of us to get behind a strong, bipartisan, bicameral bill to help workers & the economy.
Murray: We started with a House proposal & a Senate proposal, and met in the middle. That’s what the American people sent us here to do.
Murray: This bill doubles down on programs that work, and improves programs that have become outdated
Murray: We have to make sure that when high-tech jobs of the 21st Century are created – Americans are ready to fill them.
Murray: With new jobs requiring advanced skills, we'll fall behind if we don’t modernize our workforce development system & programs now
Murray: I’ve seen many #WA businesses get access to workers with new skills they need to grow and compete
Murray: In Washington State, I've seen workers who were laid off who were able to get new training, new skills, and new jobs.
Murray: Federal workforce programs have proven time and again that the best investment we can make is in American workers.
Murray: None of us got everything we wanted – but we all got a bill that will help workers, businesses, and the economy for years to come.
Murray: I’d like to thank my Senate co-authors: @SenatorIsakson, @SenatorHarkin, and @SenAlexander for their hard work on this bill
Murray: The reason this agreement was possible is the incredible, bipartisan process we’ve had over the last few months to find a compromise
Murray: I’ve heard from workers & businesses in #WA & across the country about how important effective workforce programs are.
Murray: Improving our federal workforce programs is something I’ve been working on for more than a decade.
Murray: This is a long overdue bill that will reauthorize and improve the Workforce Investment Act.

Murray: Let’s show the American people that Congress can work together to ensure vital construction projects can move forward this summer
Murray: Let’s show states that we will continue to invest in projects that help drivers and help businesses move their goods
Murray: For many states, this looming Highway Trust Fund crisis is already a reality. We need to act now.
Murray: I hope Republicans will join us, willing to close just a few loopholes to avoid an unnecessary crisis in the Highway Trust Fund
Murray: Closing wasteful loopholes so we can create jobs would be good for workers & the economy, & would make our broken tax system fairer
Murray: I hope we can find a bipartisan solution. POTUS & @RepDaveCamp have both proposed using corporate revenue to address this crisis
Murray: According to analysis by @amprog, failing to shore up the Highway Trust Fund could cost more than 180,000 jobs in fiscal year 2015
Murray: We could potentially see a construction shutdown, meaning workers would be left without a paycheck
Murray: The crisis is right around the corner, and many states are now planning for worst-case scenarios
Murray: @USDOT says the trust fund won’t be able to keep up w/ its payments to states as soon as this summer
Murray: It funds safety initiatives & construction that improves roads and bridges. And it sparks job creation for American workers
Murray: The trust fund supports transportation projects to ease congestion for commuters & businesses, to move goods quickly & efficiently
Murray: States across the country are rethinking their plans for construction because of funding uncertainty in the Highway Trust Fund
Murray: The Highway Trust Fund is vital for states to tackle much-needed transportation projects. But right now, it is running on fumes

Murray: #HiddenHeroes bill would allow injured to transfer Post-9/11 GI benefits to their dependents by exempting from length of service.
Murray: #HiddenHeroes bill will coordinate caregiver policy among the different departments to ensure quality standards of care.
Murray: #HiddenHeroes bill will require fed govt to meet unique needs of employees who are caregivers w/ flexible work arrangements.
Murray: #HiddenHeroes bill expands caregiver services to include child care, financial advice and legal counseling.
Murray: #HiddenHeroes bill expands eligibility for VA caregivers by removing restrictions & places emphasis on mental health.
Murray: #HiddenHeroes bill makes veterans of **all eras** eligible for full range of caregiver support services.
Murray: There is no way we will sit by & let caregivers face this on their own. Not when we can make it at least a little bit easier.

Murray: We must act to prevent a construction shutdown this summer, so let’s build on the common ground both parties share on this issue.
Murray: Let’s give the Highway Trust Fund some certainty, so states can keep investing in jobs and economic growth.
Murray: There is no reason to wait until the last minute to get this done. The threat is growing for construction sites & jobs.
Murray: Replenishing the fund with revenue raise by closing these loopholes will provide multi-year funding, giving states certainty
Murray: By closing wasteful corporate loopholes we can support improvements to roads and bridges that will help everyone.
Murray: There has been bipartisan support to shore up the Highway Trust Fund by using corporate revenue.
Murray: We need to ensure construction can continue this summer, support workers, & deliver a multi-year solution for the Highway Trust Fund
Murray: We must act to avoid this construction shutdown; there is no reason to lurch to an avoidable crisis when workers are struggling
Murray: If the funding isn’t resolved, construction projects could shut down, leaving workers without a paycheck
Murray: The fund helps repave roads, ease congestion on our nation’s highways, and helps repair bridges that are unsafe.
Murray: I call on all of my colleagues to work together on a solution to avert this looming crisis
Murray: A construction shutdown could ramp up when the Highway Trust Fund reaches critically low levels in just a few months.
Murray: The budget deal was a step in the right direction & we need to take more steps to ensure we don’t lurch to another avoidable crisis

Murray: Today we are taking another step forward to uphold the promise we made women & provide this access broadly. #standwithwomen #SCOTUS
Murray: Proud to be joined in this effort by 18 other Senators who know that contraception access is good health & economic policy.
Murray: Can’t allow for-profit, secular corporations to deny employees’ comprehensive health care, under guise of “religious exemption.”
Murray: Contraceptive coverage is supported by the vast majority of Americans who understand how important it is for women and families.
Murray: Every American deserves to have access to high quality health care coverage regardless of where they work.
Murray: What's at stake in this case before #SCOTUS is whether a CEO's personal beliefs can trump a woman's right to access contraception.
Murray: Allowing a woman's boss to call the shots about her access to birth control should be inconceivable in this day & age.
Murray: There are those out there who think it's a debate about "freedom," except of course the freedom for women to access care.
Murray: For this reason, today-along with 18 other members of my caucus-I will file a brief w/ #SCOTUS in #HobbyLobby case. #standwithwomen
Murray: In the past 3yrs, the US has enacted more of these restrictions than in the previous 10 YEARS combined. #standwithwomen
Murray: In 2013 we saw another record breaking year of states passing restrictive laws barring access to abortion services. #standwithwomen
Murray: #HR7 is nothing more than an attempt to eliminate access to abortion services. #StopHR7
Murray: #HR7 severely undermines a woman's access to insurance coverage of comprehensive health care. #StopHR7
